Each thread can have an [`UncaughtExceptionHandler`](https://docs.oracle.com/en/java/javase/11/docs/api/java.base/java/lang/Thread.UncaughtExceptionHandler.html), which is called when an exception reaches the bottom of the thread&#39;s call stack. The default implementation prints a message on the standard error.

You can change the default handler with:

```lang-java
  private static final Logger logger = LogManager.getLogger();

  public static void main(String[] args) throws IOException {
    Thread.setDefaultUncaughtExceptionHandler((t, e) -&gt; {
